  "texts": [
    "As a result, we have utilized a 4 d delay as our input for all deep learning models in this study to forecast the soil moisture content on the fifth day.",
    "This means the input vector I {x t-3, x t-2, x t-1, x t } is used to predict the target value y t, which is the soil moisture SM t at time t. For machine learning, we only utilize the x t to generate predictions.",
    "This study builds individual predictive models for each site and depth, disregarding the inclusion of static properties such as land cover, soil hydraulic properties, and topography.",
    "Soil moisture and soil temperature data are obtained from the ISMN.",
    "Specifically, the meteorological data applied in this work are sourced from the NASA Prediction Of Worldwide Energy Resources (POWER) project (https: //power.larc.nasa.gov/, last access: 20 February 2024), which provides a wide range of meteorological data, such as temperature, precipitation, and solar radiation."
